headline: Consumers Keep Bailing Out the Economy. Now They Might Be Maxed Out.
summary: American consumers and their credit cards have helped the U.S. economy weather many rough moments.  Now, as recession fears resurface, the worry is that they might be maxed out.  The stock market’s recent plunge has been broad.
